BRAZIL: Brazil to post $350 mln July trade gap--newspaper.Brazil to post $350 mln July trade gap--newspaper.The government is expected to report a trade deficit for July of around $350 million, about unchanged from June, a local financial newspaper said.This would bring the trade deficit for the year to date to $600 million, in line with market forecasts of a trade gap of $1-$2 billion for the full year, Gazeta Mercantil said.Exports in July amounted to around $4.46 billion, while imports were around $4.8 billion, it said.-- Simona de Logu, Rio de Janeiro Newsroom 5521 507 4151